// Reading Exercise 02-07

public static int max(int[] arr) {
  if (arr.length == 0) {
    throw new IllegalArgumentException(); // ignore this case
  } else {
  int ret = arr[0];
    for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
      if (ret < arr[i]) {
        ret = arr[i];
      }
    }
    return ret;
  }
}

4.4
Best Case: T(1) = 1
Average Case: T(n) = n/2
Worst Case: T(n) = n

4.5
Best Case: f is in the same class of functions as f(1) = 1
Average Case: f is in the same class of functions as f(n) = n
Worst Case: f is in the same class of functions as f(n) = n
